<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="4Oct1922"><font color="red">4 October 1922</font>, <cite>BLHW</cite> (JJ to Harriet Weaver): I suppose it is too late to correct: p 484 l 5 for 1882 read 1886. [&hellip;] I wonder if I shall see Mr Rodker before I leave Paris. I shall stop a half day in Dijon as six hours train is enough for me. Will you please tell him that the stupid hosier in Folkestone to whom I wrote prepaying reply did not answer so he will not have the trouble of bringing me the collars.</div>
